      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 2029: Messages for which the plugin intentionally returns no bodyOverwrite are never marked as processed, because absence of pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] is used both for \"not processed yet\" and \"processed with no overwrite\". loadMissingBodyOverwrites() will therefore re-run plugin transforms for the same messages and editions on every load/reload path, which can become very expensive for large histories. Add an explicit processed marker or cache negative results separately, and clear that marker in reloadBodyOverwriteMessages().\n```suggestion\nstatic constexpr auto BODY_OVERWRITE_KEY \u003d \"bodyOverwrite\";\nstatic constexpr auto BODY_OVERWRITE_PROCESSED_KEY \u003d \"bodyOverwriteProcessed\";\n\nbool needsWork \u003d msg-\u003epluginData.find(BODY_OVERWRITE_PROCESSED_KEY) \u003d\u003d msg-\u003epluginData.end();\n...\nrealIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[BODY_OVERWRITE_PROCESSED_KEY] \u003d \"true\";\nif (boIt !\u003d single[0].pluginData.end() \u0026\u0026 !boIt-\u003esecond.empty())\n    realIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[BODY_OVERWRITE_KEY] \u003d boIt-\u003esecond;\nelse\n    realIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.erase(BODY_OVERWRITE_KEY);\n```",
