      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 2256: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() runs only after SwarmLoaded has already been emitted, while the new ChatHandler API documents that transforms happen before SwarmLoaded. This means clients first receive untranslated bodies and then separate SwarmMessageUpdated signals, causing observable flicker and making the API contract misleading. Either move the transform before emitting SwarmLoaded, or update the API/comment to state that overwrites are delivered asynchronously after the load signal.\n```suggestion\nconv-\u003econversation-\u003eloadMessages(\n    [accountId \u003d pimpl_-\u003eaccountId_, conversationId, id, convWeak](auto\u0026\u0026 messages) {\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\n        if (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n            convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n#endif\n        emitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n    },\n    options);\n```",
